100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On November 2, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing tensions in Europe and the Middle East, particularly regarding the status of the Saar region. In the United States, the Supreme Court began hearing arguments on a landmark case concerning the regulation of interstate commerce. Meanwhile, political unrest continued in China as factions vied for control, raising concerns about stability in the region.
